data.content:
Here are the modern MSTest replacements for each assertion:

```csharp
[TestMethod]
public void GetActiveUsers_ReturnsOnlyActiveUsers()
{
    var service = new UserService();
    var users = service.GetActiveUsers();

    Assert.IsNotEmpty(users);
    Assert.IsTrue(users.All(u => u.IsActive));
    Assert.HasCount(3, users);
    var admin = Assert.ContainsSingle(users.Where(u => u.Role == "Admin"));
}
```

**What changed:**

| Before | After | Why |
|---|---|---|
| `Assert.IsTrue(users.Count > 0)` | `Assert.IsNotEmpty(users)` | Clearer failure message ("collection was empty" vs "expected True, got False") |
| `Assert.IsTrue(users.Count() == 3)` | `Assert.HasCount(3, users)` | Shows actual count on failure |
| `users.Single()` + `Assert.IsTrue(admin != null)` | `Assert.ContainsSingle(filtered)` | Asserts exactly one match and returns it |

The `users.All(u => u.IsActive)` check has no built-in collection equivalent, so `Assert.IsTrue` is fine there. These APIs require **MSTest 3.8+**.
